On 28&nbsp;August&nbsp;2008 Ornge announced the purchase of ten new [[AgustaWestland AW139]] helicopters to replace their fleet of Sikorsky S-76 helicopters,<ref name="Ornge25Aug08">{{cite press release |title= Ornge purchases new fleet of high performance medically equipped helicopters - Signals a new era in transport medicine for Ontario patients|url= http://www.ornge.ca/AW139Aug25.pdf|format= PDF|publisher= Ornge|date= 2008-08-25|accessdate= 2008-08-30}}</ref> to be delivered over a period of two years beginning in late&nbsp;2010.<ref name="Ornge8Sept08">{{cite press release |title= Ornge and Canadian Helicopters Income Fund Announce Agreement in Principle|url= http://www.ornge.ca/CHLOrngefinalrelease2.pdf |format= PDF|publisher= Ornge|date= 2008-09-03|accessdate=2009-08-20}}</ref> The S-76&nbsp;helicopters were previously owned and operated by [[Canadian Helicopters]], but are now owned by Ornge and operated by Canadian Helicopters.<ref name="chlstatement">[http://www.ornge.ca/Media/Documents/Media%20Releases/chlstatementsept30.pdf Ornge Statement on Rotor Wing Operations] {{Sic}}</ref> The S-76&nbsp;helicopters will be serviced by Canadian Helicopters until April&nbsp;2012.<ref name="chlstatement" />

